cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with improving the decoding process of sequence models, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new module to incorporate future information, which involves machine learning techniques such as maximum likelihood and value networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses OCR image to LaTeX and machine translation datasets, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a solution to the end-of-sentence (EOS) problem, which is a common issue in neural network-based models, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
